E
history~

     This book tells much of the ancient Spellseers.  It covers
     everthing from the bloodline of family magic-users to the
     Year of the Whistling Wind.  In that year the Spellseer
     house came to a fall.  As the castle prospered in fortune
     and grew to have good ties with the royal family of Amn,
     other rich families became envious of them.  Eventually
     envy lead to the forgery of documents implementing the
     Spellseers as using their magical abilities to an unfair
     advantage over their trading partners.  In the time that
     followed the royal family turned against the Spellseers,
     along with many of the lands merchants.  The Spellseers
     had fallen.

~
E
Spulzeer~

     The Spulseers..
     In the year 838, a youthful but wise Spellseer patriarch,
     Tregas II, changed the family name to "Spulzeer" in an
     attempt to restore the good name and profits of the clan.
     He instituted other reforms, dropped a cloak of total
     secrecy around the family's magical practices, and curried
     favor with the King of Amn by loaning money to the crown
     at no interest.  His plan was successful, and by 900DR,
     Spulzeer was a family to be reckoned with.  "Spellseer"
     was beginning to be forgotten.

~
E
Guide~

     What parts of this guide you can understand refers to the
     changing of ones self and rituals needed to become a lich.
     Some of the pages appear to be missing.

